In this episode, Liam Morrissey, Chief Executive Officer at MS Risk, a global security risk management consultancy that specialises in identifying, mitigating and reducing security risk discusses the conflict situation currently unfolding in Burkina Faso and the greater Sahel region in West Africa and the impact thereof on the regional mining sector. We also take a closer look at the risk that the COVID-19 pandemic is having on the country already marred by ongoing conflict. And remember, you can access all our podcasts, webinars, videos, industry insights and the latest mining news at miningreview.com You can subscribe to Spotify or Apple Podcasts directly for easy listening. 